    <stitle>7.3 Liter Diesel Engine Service (1991) - INJECTION PUMP, NOZZLES, FUEL FILTER, SUPPLY PUMP AND GLOW PLUGS -
        FUEL SUPPLY PUMP (Removal and Reassembly) (All applications) - REMOVAL
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="proctype" graphiccount="8">
        <title>REMOVAL</title>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Loosen all 8 fuel injection line connecting nuts at nozzles using an open end wrench. Refer
                to
                <emph type="bold">Figure
                    <hotlnk xrefid="ef4350930">9.30</hotlnk>.
                </emph>
            </para>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>It is not necessary to remove injection lines from injection pump to remove injection pump. If
                        lines are to be removed, loosen injection line fittings at injection pump before removing it
                        from engine.
                    </para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the adapter housing oil fill tube or cover plate,
                <emph type="bold">Figure
                    <hotlnk xrefid="ef4350931">9.31</hotlnk>
                </emph>
                , to access the injection pump drive gear mounting bolts. (1988 Model Year and prior, shown in
                <emph type="bold">Figure
                    <hotlnk xrefid="ef4350931">9.31</hotlnk>
                </emph>
                . 1989 Model Year and beyond uses a cover plate.)
            </para>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>The oil fill tube is sealed with R.T.V. sealant. There is no gasket.</para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>Cover plate is sealed with R.T.V. sealant. There is NO gasket.</para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
            <figure id="ef4350929" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="cg11173" filename="../figcg1/CG11173.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 9.29</caption>
            </figure>
            <figure id="ef4350930" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="cg11174" filename="../figcg1/CG11174.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 9.30</caption>
            </figure>
            <figure id="ef4350931" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="cg12391" filename="../figcg1/CG12391.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 9.31</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove injection pump drive gear mounting bolts (
                <emph type="bold">Figure
                    <hotlnk xrefid="ef4350932">9.32</hotlnk>
                </emph>
                ) using a 5/16 in.12 pt. socket.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Disconnect the electrical connectors at the injection pump.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the fast idle solenoid bracket assembly (
                <emph type="bold">Figure
                    <hotlnk xrefid="ef4350933">9.33</hotlnk>
                </emph>
                )
                <emph type="bold"></emph>to provide access to the injection pump mounting nuts.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the fuel return hose and clip from the 90&#176; elbow at the governor cover. Cap
                opening at the governor cover elbow. Refer to
                <emph type="bold">Figure
                    <hotlnk xrefid="ef4350934">9.34</hotlnk>
                </emph>
                .
            </para>
            <figure id="ef4350932" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="cg12392" filename="../figcg1/CG12392.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 9.32</caption>
            </figure>
            <figure id="ef4350933" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="cg12395" filename="../figcg1/CG12395.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 9.33</caption>
            </figure>
            <figure id="ef4350934" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="cg12396" filename="../figcg1/CG12396.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 9.34</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the filter to injection pump tube (17,
                <emph type="bold">Figure
                    <hotlnk document="e435_171.xml" xrefid="ef4350911">9.11</hotlnk>
                </emph>
                ) as described in this section under "Fuel Filter Assembly - Removal". Cap the pump opening.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Using injection pump wrench
                <emph type="bold">ZTSE4132</emph>, remove injection pump mounting nuts and washers to adapter housing as
                shown in
                <emph type="bold">Figure
                    <hotlnk xrefid="ef4350935">9.35</hotlnk>.
                </emph>
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Lift injection pump with high pressure lines from the mounting studs on the adapter housing.
                Refer to
                <emph type="bold">Figure
                    <hotlnk xrefid="ef4350936">9.36</hotlnk>
                </emph>
                . Install protective caps on the high pressure lines and nozzles.
                <emph type="bold"></emph>
            </para>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>If injection pump is to be replaced, remove injection lines at pump, with pump and lines
                        removed as an assembly, using fuel line wrench ZTSE4133. Cap all fittings using the protective
                        cap set ZTSE4135. Install fuel lines to the injection pump prior to installing the injection
                        pump on the engine.
                    </para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
            <figure id="ef4350935" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="cg12397a" filename="../figcg1/CG12397A.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 9.35</caption>
            </figure>
            <figure id="ef4350936" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="cg12398" filename="../figcg1/CG12398.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 9.36</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
